---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import SocialShare from '../components/SocialShare.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="Privacy Policy for CloudyUnicorn Tools. Learn how we protect your data with our 100% client-side calculation philosophy."
>
  <div class="relative min-h-[calc(100vh-16rem)] bg-background py-16 sm:py-24">
    <!-- Grid Background -->
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-grid-pattern bg-grid-fade pointer-events-none opacity-20"></div>

    <div class="relative max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 space-y-12 animate-fade-in">
      <!-- Breadcrumbs -->
      <nav aria-label="Breadcrumb" class="flex items-center gap-2 text-xs font-mono text-neutral-500">
        <a href="/" class="hover:text-neutral-600 dark:hover:text-neutral-300">Tools</a>
        <span>/</span>
        <span class="text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300">Privacy Policy</span>
      </nav>

      <!-- Page Header -->
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-5xl font-bold tracking-tight text-neutral-900 dark:text-white">
          Privacy Policy
        </h1>
        <p class="text-neutral-400 text-xs sm:text-sm font-mono">
          Last Updated: June 16, 2026 &bull; Effective Immediately
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Main Content Block -->
      <div class="prose prose-neutral dark:prose-invert max-w-none text-sm text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-400 space-y-8 leading-relaxed font-light">
        
        <p>
          Welcome to CloudyUnicorn Tools. Your privacy is of paramount importance to us. This privacy policy describes the practices, terms, and guidelines regarding how we handle data on our web platform. We believe in absolute transparency, and our primary goal is to provide useful utilities without harvesting your personal information.
        </p>

        <!-- Crucial Callout -->
        <div class="border border-dashed border-neutral-300 dark:border-neutral-800 bg-neutral-50/50 dark:bg-neutral-900/10 p-5 rounded-xl flex items-start gap-4">
          <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-brand-green shrink-0 mt-0.5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 12l2 2 4-4m5.618-4.016A11.955 11.955 0 0112 2.944a11.955 11.955 0 01-8.618 3.04A12.02 12.02 0 003 9c0 5.591 3.824 10.29 9 11.622 5.176-1.332 9-6.03 9-11.622 0-1.042-.133-2.052-.382-3.016z"></path>
          </svg>
          <div class="space-y-1">
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white text-xs font-mono uppercase tracking-wider">Our Privacy Guarantee</h3>
            <p class="text-xs">
              CloudyUnicorn Tools is designed to run <strong>100% client-side</strong>. We do not store, collect, or transmit any variables (such as age, birthdates, heights, weights, or daily habits) that you input into our calculators. All calculations happen inside your browser context.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <section class="space-y-3">
          <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white tracking-tight">1. Data We Do Not Collect (Local Processing)</h2>
          <p>
            The core architecture of our website relies on localized client-side execution. When you calculate metrics using the Age Calculator, BMI Calculator, or Calories Calculator, the inputs are processed in real-time by JavaScript running directly on your computer, tablet, or smartphone.
          </p>
          <p>
            Because we do not use server-side script pipelines for calculating your results, the following parameters remain entirely private:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-1.5 text-neutral-500">
            <li><strong>No Input Logs:</strong> Input parameters such as dates of birth, exact weights, daily calorie targets, height metrics, or health stats are never transmitted over the internet to our systems.</li>
            <li><strong>No Database Storage:</strong> We do not operate database servers to log, profile, or retain histories of your calculation logs.</li>
            <li><strong>No Account Creation:</strong> You can access all calculator features without creating an account, registering an email, or linking a social media profile.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="space-y-3">
          <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white tracking-tight">2. Server Logs and Hosting Infrastructure</h2>
          <p>
            Like almost all websites on the internet, our hosting infrastructure automatically collects standard, non-identifying server request logs. This is necessary to deliver the static website files (HTML, CSS, JS, and image assets) to your browser.
          </p>
          <p>
            These server logs may record basic metadata such as your IP address, browser user agent, requested pages, reference links, and the date and time of the request. We use this technical data strictly to monitor infrastructure health, optimize assets loading speeds, prevent DDoS attacks, and block malicious traffic. This server-level logging is completely separate from the calculators and cannot be linked to any numerical inputs you enter.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="space-y-3">
          <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white tracking-tight">3. Cookies and Browser Storage Policy</h2>
          <p>
            Our privacy policy dictates that we do not deploy advertising cookies, behavioral tracking scripts, or cross-site tracking systems. We value a clean web experience.
          </p>
          <p>
            However, we may utilize standard web browser local storage (`localStorage`) to remember your visual style preferences. For instance, when you toggle the dark mode button on the interface, your preference is saved locally on your device so that subsequent visits default to your chosen theme. This theme state is never sent to our servers and can be wiped instantly by clearing your browser cache or site data.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="space-y-3">
          <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white tracking-tight">4. Third-Party Integrations and Links</h2>
          <p>
            We do not load third-party ad networks, marketing trackers, or social sharing plugins that collect background metrics. Any social sharing options presented on our site are built locally using clean outbound HTML sharing templates that do not track you.
          </p>
          <p>
            Our web pages may contain outbound links to other standalone projects or digital assets in our ecosystem (such as `alcoholdetect.com`). When you leave our domain, this privacy policy no longer applies. We recommend reviewing the individual privacy policies of external sites to understand their data collection methods.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="space-y-3">
          <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white tracking-tight">5. User Rights (GDPR & CCPA Compliance)</h2>
          <p>
            Under frameworks like the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) and the California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA), users are granted rights regarding their personal data, including the right to view, modify, or erase their stored details.
          </p>
          <p>
            Because CloudyUnicorn Tools processes calculations entirely inside your local browser context and stores no personal records on server databases, we do not possess any of your private information. Consequently, we cannot retrieve, export, delete, or modify your calculation history on your behalf, as we do not have access to it. Your data is owned and held exclusively by you on your local machine.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="space-y-3">
          <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white tracking-tight">6. Revisions to this Policy</h2>
          <p>
            We may update our privacy guidelines from time to time as we roll out new calculators, tools, and updates. Any changes will be published directly on this page, and the revision timestamp at the top of the policy will be updated accordingly. We encourage users to check this page periodically to remain informed about our privacy standards.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="space-y-3">
          <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white tracking-tight">7. Contact and Support Details</h2>
          <p>
            If you have any questions, concerns, or inquiries regarding our data handling or this privacy policy, please contact our support desk via email at <!--email_off--><a href="mailto:privacy@cloudyunicorn.com" class="text-neutral-950 dark:text-white hover:underline font-medium">privacy@cloudyunicorn.com</a><!--/email_off-->.
          </p>
        </section>

      </div>

      <!-- Social Sharing Options -->
      <div class="mt-12 pt-8 border-t border-neutral-200 dark:border-neutral-800">
        <SocialShare shareText="Check out this privacy-first online tools platform by CloudyUnicorn Tools!" />
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>

<style>
  @keyframes fadeIn {
    from {
      opacity: 0;
      transform: translateY(8px);
    }
    to {
      opacity: 1;
      transform: translateY(0);
    }
  }

  .animate-fade-in {
    animation: fadeIn 0.5s cubic-bezier(0.16, 1, 0.3, 1) forwards;
  }
</style>
